From: j0yen <jyen.tech@gmail.com>
Date: 2026-05-24
Subject: [PATCH 09/10] proc/ns: register agentns_operations

Add agentns_operations to the namespace ops table so /proc/$PID/ns/agent
appears alongside the standard seven namespaces, and nsenter / lsns
learn to enumerate it.

Signed-off-by: j0yen <jyen.tech@gmail.com>
---
 fs/proc/namespaces.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

--- a/fs/proc/namespaces.c
+++ b/fs/proc/namespaces.c
@@ -16,6 +16,9 @@
 #include <linux/pid_namespace.h>
 #include <linux/user_namespace.h>
 #include <net/net_namespace.h>
+#ifdef CONFIG_AGENT_NS
+#include <linux/agent_namespaces.h>
+#endif

 #include "internal.h"

@@ -36,6 +39,9 @@ static const struct proc_ns_operations *ns_entries[] = {
 #endif
 #ifdef CONFIG_TIME_NS
 	&timens_operations,
+#endif
+#ifdef CONFIG_AGENT_NS
+	&agentns_operations,
 #endif
 };
